'''''Colorful Dragon''''' ({{zh|t=變色龍|p=Biànsèlóng|l=Chameleon}}), is a [[List of maze video games|maze game]] developed and published by [[Thin Chen Enterprise|Sachen]] for the [[Nintendo Entertainment System]] on 1989 in Asia. [[Bunch Games]] later licensed the game for distribution in [[North America]] for a 1990 release, and published it as '''''Tagin' Dragon'''''.

Sachen republished ''Colorful Dragon'' in the multi-game cartridge ''Super Cartridge Version 6: 6-in-1''.

==Gameplay==
In the game, the player controls a [[European dragon]], and attempts to bite the tails off other European dragons. The longer a dragon's tail, the more bites required to defeat it. There are 20 mazes.

Two players may play either competitively or [[Cooperative video game|cooperatively]].

